					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11210200#post-4223886</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11210200/scp-4294#post-4223886</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Apr 2019 18:20:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MobRules</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2234247</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Agreed!</p> <p>Though it's a bit confusing when it says they should continue to track 4294 even when 4294 isn't there&#8230; perhaps use 4294-# sub-designations, like 4294-1 for the weird giant flesh, 4294-2 for the old woman, and 4294-3 for the unseasonable blizzard? So that it's clear what is de-manifesting and what is being tracked.</p> <p>I didn't expect to like this &#8212; at first, it seemed to be wtf-for-wtf-sake-silly, but it all came together in the end. +1.</p> <p>I feel bad for the guys that got turned into newts for not realizing that by &quot;Maxine&quot; she actually meant &quot;Vladimir&quot;&#8230;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
